Arthur Levitt , former chairman of the
U.S. Securities and Exchange Commission and senior adviser to 
Goldman Sachs, says derivatives are "very positive for our 
markets and have gotten a black eye" after a $2 billion loss by 
JPMorgan Chase.  Levitt talks with Bloomberg's Ken Prewitt and 
Tom Keene on Bloomberg Radio's "Bloomberg Surveillance."     (Source: Bloomberg)  Running time 06:21
 